\newlabel{fig:sector}{{3}{6}{Source$\to $target sector density per period (transfer entropy, log-price; rows = source sector, columns = target sector). The absence of a consistently dominant diagonal indicates that within-sector density is not systematically higher than between-sector density.\relax }{figure.caption.12}{}}
